reviews.review_text: RHB There is a reason they only played it once. We used to call it Revolutionary Horsesh*t Blues.  You know how we can get when we are 17 years old and dissatisfied/spoiled deadheads.  Anyway, an overall good show and Joe's recordings rock.

Agreed I was there and 17 myself, did this whole tour except first two spectrum/rectum shows.  Great times.  But yeah, this song was simply a waste of time, i just kind of stood there and watched.  loved cumberland country, i think the band did too.  I was there in '85 as well in the snow and day tripper, etc.  Fantastic.  SOlid show, the Kaiser shows for Chinese new years were gerat, this tour had a cuple moments, greeks were solid then the summer tour Garcia really hit a wall.
